points.name: MCV
points.abnormality: Above normal range Result Comment MCV result discrepant from previous result. Measured MCV may be affected by abnormalities in plasma osmolarity, red cell transfusion or red cell agglutination. If no apparent reason for discrepancy, suggest recollection. Macrocytosis. May be due to Vitamin B12 or folate deficiency, liver disease, hypothyroidism or drug effect. In older individuals, consider myelodysplasia if persistent & accompanied by cytopenia(s).
